

=Bio=

"Dale Dougherty is the founder of Make magazine and the creator of Maker Faire. He is GM of Maker Media at O’Reilly Media in Sebastopol, California. Dougherty is a co-founder of O’Reilly Media, a technical publisher and conference organizer known for its advocacy of Open Source and the Web. Dale was the developer of Global Network Navigator, the first commercial Web site launched in 1993. He coined the term Web 2.0 as part of developing the Web 2.0 Conference."


